The paper deals with the problem of stabilizing a linear system over a timing channel, which involves communication and information theory aspects (cs.IT), as well as control theory (cs.SY). The use of phone calls as an analogy suggests a potential connection to networking and communication systems (cs.NI). The paper also uses random-coding strategies, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization (cs.MA), and the results generalize previous event-triggering control approaches, which may relate to machine learning and statistical inference (cs.LG).
